, Vice President, External Relations and Social Responsibility




Nick Cotts was elected Vice President, External Relations and Social Responsibility in February 2016, after having served as Group Executive – External Relations since 2013 and Group Executive – Environment and Social Responsibility from 2011 to 2013.  Mr. Cotts began his career at Newmont as Manager of Environmental Affairs in Newmont’s South America region in 1994.  Throughout his over twenty year career with Newmont, he has served in various roles in the areas of environmental affairs, communications, external affairs, social responsibility, stakeholder engagement and sustainability.  Mr. Cotts has worked at numerous Newmont operations across the globe, with over 17 years of experience working at our Peru and Ghana operations. He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Agronomy – Soil Conservation and a Master of Science degree in Range Science – Restoration Ecology, both from Colorado State University. 






Mary Beth Donnelly
